properties.name: HCJB
properties.description: Posted by Generation274Quito, EcuadorI visited Ecuador in 2001. If there was a place I could go now, other than Italy, I would go to Ecuador. I love that country. I worked with a church that is next door to HCJB headquarters. Quito is the capital city of Ecuador and the equator passes right through it!

properties.name: Helsinki, Finland, HEL
properties.description: Posted by Generation274I had a memorable stay in Helsinki when I was traveling back from Russia in 1996. Our group got bumped from out original flight because a former US president was flying. (I don\'t know the details). We were given some cash and free stay at a 5 star hotel, which was great fun.

properties.name: Novgorod
properties.description: Posted by Generation274Novgorod, RussiaI visisted Russia in 1996 with my church. We worked with a church in Novgorod. We also visited St. Petersburg, which used to be called Leningrad, I think. There was a lot of communism stuff still around then. I expect it is very different by now.

properties.description: Posted by Generation274San DiegoI lived here before I lived in Argentina. I have a few memories of earthquakes, I think I must have been 3 or 4 years old.

properties.description: Posted by Generation274torontoI have been to Toronto many times, mostly to see a musical or show. Great fun! Once I went to visit the Toronto airport church, but to visit a friend, not to attend a service, unfortunatly.
